👉 Constructors in Inheritance

When a Derived class is extended from the Base class the constructor of the Base class is executed first followed by the constructor 
of the derived class.

For the following Inheritance Hierarchy, the constructors are executed in the order {1}->{2}->{3}

C1 --> Parent
⬇️
C2 --> Child                                     ⬇️ Contructors execute in top to bottom order!
⬇️
C3 --> Grand Child

class Base{
    Base(){
        System.out.println("Constructor of BASE class");
    }
}
class Derived extends Base{
    Derived(){
        System.out.println("Constructor of Derived class");
    }
}
public class Inheritance{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Base b = new Base();
        Derived d = new Derived();
    }
}


Output : 

Constructor of BASE class
Constructor of BASE class
Constructor of Derived class

Process finished with exit code 0

