👉 Overloaded Constructor in Inheritance

When there are multiple constructors in the parent class, the constructor without any parameters is called from the child class. If we
want to call the constructor with parameters from the parent class . We can use { super } keyword 

super(a,b); --> calls the constructor from the parent class which takes 2 variables

Example 

class Base{
    Base(){
        System.out.println("Constructor of BASE class");
    }
    Base(int a){
        System.out.println("Overloaded Constructor with value : "+a);
    }
}
class Derived extends Base{
    Derived(int x , int y){
        super(0);
        System.out.println("Constructor of Derived class with value x: "+x);
        System.out.println("Constructor of Derived class with value y: "+y);
    }
}
public class Inheritance{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Derived d = new Derived(14,15);
    }
}


Output : 
Overloaded Constructor with value : 0
Constructor of Derived class with value x: 14
Constructor of Derived class with value y: 15

Process finished with exit code 0
